# Part 2

## Describe a TV show/online program you have watched recently.

Recently, I watched an online program called *The Three-Body Problem*, which is a science-fiction series adapted from a very famous Chinese novel. I watched it on an online streaming platform during my spare time after studying.

The story is mainly about humanity’s first contact with an alien civilization and how advanced technology, physics, and human nature interact in extreme situations. What I really like about the show is that it combines scientific theories with philosophical questions. It’s not just about space or aliens; it also explores topics like morality, survival, trust, and the future of human civilization.

I’ve watched several episodes over the past few weeks, usually at night after finishing my university assignments. Since I’m quite interested in artificial intelligence and technology, I found many parts of the series especially fascinating. Some scenes about scientific experiments and future technologies really stimulated my imagination.

To be honest, I think the program is much more meaningful than ordinary entertainment shows because it encourages viewers to think deeply. The acting and visual effects are also impressive, and the atmosphere feels very immersive.

However, I have to admit that sometimes the plot is a little complicated, especially if you don’t have much background knowledge in science. Still, I think that challenge actually makes the show more engaging.

Overall, I really enjoyed watching it because it was intellectually stimulating, emotionally intense, and visually impressive at the same time. It’s definitely one of the best online programs I’ve watched recently.

---

### 中文翻译：

最近我看了一部叫《三体》的网络剧，它改编自一部非常著名的中国科幻小说。我是在学习之余，通过在线视频平台观看的。

这部剧主要讲述了人类第一次接触外星文明，以及先进科技、物理学和人性在极端环境下的相互影响。我特别喜欢的一点是，它把科学理论和哲学问题结合在了一起。它不仅仅是在讲太空或者外星人，还探讨了道德、生存、信任以及人类文明未来等话题。

过去几周里，我断断续续看了好几集，通常是在晚上完成大学作业之后。因为我本身对人工智能和科技很感兴趣，所以我觉得剧里很多内容都特别吸引我。有些关于科学实验和未来科技的场景，真的很能激发我的想象力。

说实话，我觉得这部剧比普通娱乐节目更有意义，因为它会促使观众深入思考。演员表现和视觉特效也都非常出色，整体氛围很有沉浸感。

不过我也得承认，有时候剧情确实有点复杂，尤其是对于没有科学背景的人来说。但我觉得这种挑战反而让它更加吸引人。

总的来说，我真的很喜欢这部剧，因为它既能启发思考，又情绪张力很强，而且视觉效果也很震撼。绝对是我最近看过最好的网络节目之一。

